-! # how to errors: 046-spawn-outside-nursery.zo
-!
-! @cmd: `zo build 046-spawn-outside-nursery.zo`
-!
-! Per `PLAN_CHANNELS.md` Phase 0 decision 3, `spawn` only
-! makes sense inside a `nursery { }` — the nursery is
-! what owns the spawned task's lifetime, guarantees the
-! join on scope exit, and routes panics to the parent.
-!
-! A bare `spawn f()` at function level has no parent to
-! anchor to, so zo rejects it at compile time rather than
-! silently inventing an implicit nursery.

fun worker() {}

fun main() {
  spawn worker();
}
